descript.purpose: This digital, geographically referenced data set was developed by the Iowa Department of Natural Resources to carry out agency responsibilities related to management, protection, and development of Iowa's natural resources.
descript.abstract: Public_lakes_watersheds are the delineated drainage areas to Iowa public lakes. The layer was created using the contour lines from geo-referenced topoquad maps and the HUC 12-digit boundaries.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows 2000 Version 5.0 (Build 2195) Service Pack 4; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.0.0.535

procstep.procdesc: The public lakes were located using the public_lakes.shp. 1:24K topoquad scanned maps were used for digitizing the public lakes watershed boundaries. The 12-digit HUC boundaries shapefile was used to determine the lake watershed boundaries. All lake watershed boundaries were "snapped" to 12-digit HUC boundaries if they were in relative proximity. All digitizing was done below a scale of 1:15000.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

overview.eaover:
LAKE_ID: The lake identification number as recognized by the Iowa State University Limnology Lab. This Lab samples all of Iowa's public lakes. Most of these numbers are ordered by alphabetical order of lake_name, starting with Arbor Lake.
LAKE_NAME: The full name of the lake as recognized by the IDNR.
COUNTY: The county that most of the lake watershed's lake is within.
AREA: The area of the watershed in square meters.
PERIMETER: The perimeter of the watershed in meters.
ACRE: The total acreage of the watershed.
